Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on
medium heat. Once hot, add the @butter{2%tsp} and allow to melt.

Add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally,
until golden and soft, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} to the onion for
the last min of fry time.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the
@baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Add the baby plum tomatoes to a medium #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat and spread out in a
single layer. Roast on the middle shelf of your #oven{} until softened,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, once the onion has softened, add the @diced chorizo{60%grams} to the
pan and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the chorizo has browned, stir in the garlic and @cajun spice mix{1%sachet}.
Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @basmati rice{150%grams} into the chorizo and onions until coated,
~{1%minute}.

Add the @water{300%ml} and @chicken stock paste{20%grams} to the pan, bring to
the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to
cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Zest
and cut the @lemon{1/2} into wedges.

Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another
#frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry for
~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.
Cook so they're opaque in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, stir in the cooked prawns, @red pepper chilli jelly{25%grams},
roasted tomatoes and half the parsley. Add a squeeze of lemon juice from a
lemon wedge and gently stir together.

Taste and add @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lemon juice if needed.

Spoon the Cajun prawn and chorizo rice into your #serving bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}, then sprinkle with the
remaining parsley and the lemon zest.

Serve any remaining lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!